column8:
I just finished this game,which was one of the few Silent Hill games I never played (Book of Memories and Arcade are the others),and I can really say that I didn't miss anything by playing it this late.A terrible port and such a bad Silent Hill game.

[b]PROS[/b]:
- Good soundtrack;
- Scary atmosphere;
- Good sound design;
- Okay voice acting;
- Monster design (which is probably the best part of it);
- Various narrative choices;
- Really well done Otherworld and dimension switch;
- Alex;
- Makes you truly love Silent Hill Downpour.

[b]CONS[/b]:
- Almost no true exploration,not even in the town;
- Hitboxes and enemy stunlock attacks;
- QTEs (f*ck those ferals especially in the streets);
- Terrible performances and visuals that are partially fixed by some patches (good bless these modders).Resident Evil 2 Remake runs 10x better;
- Puzzles design (they even decided to repeat the same puzzles more than one time...);
- Animations and models that,absurdly,can't even keep up with Silent Hill 3 (a game from 2003) AT ALL;
- Stupid,not interesting and not tense fights against other humans;
- Aiming mechanics (just use the knife the entire game and you will never regret it);
- Predictable and rushed story (didn't keep me interested at all) with such an empty,full of questions and unsatisfiying ending (atleast the one I got);
- It's so bad that they didn't even translate the menus in other languages so I could not use my language or I would have missed some options;
- Too short (my total time is mostly about me trying to make it work and run decently) and don't really give you more reasons to play it;
- Many boring and kind of annoying levels;
- It still cost 19.99 with no sale.


I could probably say more cons but I stop here,this should be enough for you to have an idea about this game (and why you should stay away from it unless you are truly ready for the pain).I know some people that can appreciate it (these people exist for everything,even for Resident Evil Umbrella Corps) but as a huge fan of this hystorical franchise I truly HATED IT,who put this game over Downpour deserve a floor in hell.
I give it a really generous [b]5.9/10[/b] - Watch a Youtube playthrough of who play this game well,it's better time spent.Even the old Java mobile games made me more intrigued.

